<!-- ── HOW IT WORKS ───────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="how-section" id="how-it-works">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header reveal">
      <p class="eyebrow">How it works</p>
      <h2 class="section-title" style="font-size:clamp(32px,4vw,48px);">
        A structured workflow for every <em>monthly cycle</em>
      </h2>
      <p class="section-body">
        NavBridge replaces the manual process of copying figures from fund manager PDFs
        into a master spreadsheet. Each run produces a verified, auditable update in under
        ten minutes — with every extraction traceable to source text.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="steps-grid reveal reveal-d1">
      <div class="step-card">
        <div class="step-card-num">01</div>
        <div class="step-card-title"><em>Upload</em> your master</div>
        <p class="step-card-body">
          Drop your master valuation spreadsheet and source files — PDFs, emails,
          capital account statements — from each underlying fund manager.
        </p>
        <span class="step-card-tag">Accepts PDF &amp; email</span>
      </div>
      <div class="step-card">
        <div class="step-card-num">02</div>
        <div class="step-card-title">Firm <em>detection</em></div>
        <p class="step-card-body">
          NavBridge identifies which manager each document belongs to via sender domain
          whitelist, body markers, or LLM inference — automatically, without manual tagging.
        </p>
        <span class="step-card-tag">Deterministic first</span>
      </div>
      <div class="step-card">
        <div class="step-card-num">03</div>
        <div class="step-card-title">LLM <em>extraction</em></div>
        <p class="step-card-body">
          Per-firm YAML profiles encode exactly what to extract — share class names, period
          format, value labels, sanity ranges. Claude extracts using a forced tool schema
          that rejects any structural deviation.
        </p>
        <span class="step-card-tag">Profile-driven</span>
      </div>
      <div class="step-card">
        <div class="step-card-num">04</div>
        <div class="step-card-title">Citation <em>verification</em></div>
        <p class="step-card-body">
          Every extracted value must carry a verbatim quote from the source document.
          A deterministic check confirms that exact text appears in the parsed source.
          Fabricated figures cannot pass this gate.
        </p>
        <span class="step-card-tag">Anti-hallucination</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="steps-grid-row2 reveal reveal-d2">
      <div class="step-card">
        <div class="step-card-num">05</div>
        <div class="step-card-title">Risk <em>assessment</em></div>
        <p class="step-card-body">
          A rules engine surfaces HIGH and MEDIUM findings: entity mismatches,
          material movements, downgrade protection flags, new-row creation, and
          missing sender whitelists. HIGHs are auto-blocked; MEDIUMs are
          operator decisions.
        </p>
        <span class="step-card-tag">Rules engine</span>
      </div>
      <div class="step-card">
        <div class="step-card-num">06</div>
        <div class="step-card-title">Two-gate <em>approval</em></div>
        <p class="step-card-body">
          You review the proposed updates and approve the data. NavBridge recalculates
          the master (Price, YTD, derived cells via LibreOffice headless) and shows
          you a CSV preview. You approve the CSVs. Both gates are yours.
        </p>
        <span class="step-card-tag">Human in the loop</span>
      </div>
      <div class="step-card">
        <div class="step-card-num">07</div>
        <div class="step-card-title"><em>Download</em> &amp; load</div>
        <p class="step-card-body">
          Download the updated master spreadsheet and two CSV load files —
          Load File A and Load File B — formatted for your downstream portfolio
          and risk systems. Every run is logged, timestamped, and archived.
        </p>
        <span class="step-card-tag">Ready for downstream</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

